# Pennywise Project Rules

# Command Line Rules
- Use PowerShell's semicolon (;) for command separation, not &&
- Example: git checkout main; git pull
- Always use explicit paths relative to workspace root

# Git Rules
- Branch naming: feature/<issue-number>-<description>
- Commit format: <type>(<scope>): <description> (#<issue-number>)
- Types: feat, fix, chore, docs, style, refactor, test
- Always include issue number in commits and PRs
- PR title should match commit message

# Code Style
- Python: Use Google-style docstrings
- Python: 88 character line length (Black formatter)
- Python: Double quotes for strings
- Python: 4 spaces indentation
- Keep functions focused and small
- Add type hints to function parameters

# Project Structure
/src
  /data_import      # Data import and processing
  /categorization   # Transaction categorization
/data
  /examples         # Example data files
  /processed        # Processed data files
/tests             # Test files

# Security Rules
- No credentials in code
- Use .env for environment variables
- .env is never committed to git
- Example files must use dummy data

# Documentation
- README.md in each directory
- Clear function/class documentation
- Example usage in docstrings 